<p class="paragraph-text">Paying tribute on Wednesday, Daniel&#x27;s family said he was &quot;a wonderful child&quot; who was &quot;well loved&quot; and &quot;hard working&quot; - and that his death &quot;leaves a gaping wound in the family&quot;.</p><p class="paragraph-text">&quot;No family should have to go through what we are experiencing today,&quot; they told Sky News. &quot;Any family will understand it&#x27;s an absolute tragedy.&quot;</p><p class="paragraph-text">Family friends Janti Charalambous and Ade Caxton-Cole also paid tribute to him.</p>
    

    

    

